"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Rohanese"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Runes"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sarati"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Silvan Elvish"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sindarin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sub-creation"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Taliska"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Telerin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tengwar"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Lhammas"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Tree of Tongues"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The War of the Jewels"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Valarin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Valinorean Quenya"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Valmaric script"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Vanyarin Quenya"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Welsh"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "West Avarin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Westron"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Wolf-language"}, {"ns": 0, "*": "Skirditaila"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Avarin words"}], "templates": [{"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Stub"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Maintenance"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Maintenance/styles.css"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Blockquote"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Quote"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Quote/styles.css"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Languages"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:References"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:WJ"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:PE"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Webcite"}], "images": ["CdxIconEdit.svg"], "wikitext": {"*": "{{Stub}}\n\n'''Avarin''' is a term used to refer to the combined languages of the [[Avari]].\n\n== History ==\nThere were at least six different languages, or dialects, in the Avarin group.<ref name=Author>{{WJ|Author}}, Note 9, p. 410</ref> The various dialects did not have a common development,<ref name=PE19>{{PE|19}}, pp. 18-28</ref> although all descended from [[Primitive Quendian]].<ref name=Author/>\n\nThree larger divisions of Avarin are recorded: '''West Avarin''', '''North Avarin''', and '''East Avarin'''. The West Avarin group was nearest to the [[Eldarin]] languages of the west; North Avarin was very peculiar, with no initial consonant groups. Not much is known of East Avarin.<ref name=PE19/>\n\n== Etymology ==\n''Avarin'' is a [[Quenya]] word derived from the elements ''[[avar]]'' (\"Refuser, Elf who did not journey to Aman\") + ''[[in]]'' (\"-ian, racial-adjective, language\").<ref>{{webcite|author=Paul Strack|articleurl=https://eldamo.org/content/words/word-2742492563.html|articlename=Q. '''Avarin'' pn.|website=[[Eldamo]]|accessed=31 August 2022}}</ref>\n\n== Other versions of the legendarium ==\nThe West, North, and East '''Lemberin''' tongues was a name within the early versions of the [[legendarium]] for what would later be called the West, North, and East Avarin languages.<ref>{{PE|19}}, p. 5</ref> They were originally intended to have a resemblance in sound to Goidelic, Baltic, and Finnic languages.<ref>{{webcite|author=[[David Salo]]|articleurl=https://tolkienlistsearch.herokuapp.com/message/5e9c3600df6700ce9c85bef3|articlename=Elven-latin: Part 1 of 4|dated=2022-02-06|website=[[Elfling]]|accessed=2022-09-22}}</ref>\n\n== Early etymology ==\n''Lemberin'' is a [[Quenya]] word derived from the elements ''[[lembi]]'' (\"Those That Lingered\") + ''[[in]]'' (\"-ian, racial-adjective, language\").<ref>{{webcite|author=Paul Strack|articleurl=https://eldamo.org/content/words/word-3582813311.html|articlename=Q. '''Lemberin'' pn.|website=[[Eldamo]]|accessed=31 August 2022}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[:Category:Avarin words|Avarin words]]\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://folk.uib.no/hnohf/avarin.htm Avarin: All Six Words]\n\n{{Languages}}\n\n{{References}}\n\n[[Category:Elvish]]\n[[de:Avarin]]\n[[fr:encyclo/langues/avarin]]\n[[fi:Avarin kielet]]"}}}